column1: #Text=Wikinews interviews Australian sit skier Lincoln Budge
#Text=Recently , Wikinews spent time with with Australian Paralympic skier Lincoln Budge who was in Copper Mountain , Colorado for this week 's IPC Nor-Am Cup .
#Text=I 'm interviewing Lincoln Budge , one of Australia 's development team skiers , who is here at the IPC [ International Paralympic Committee ]
#Text=Nor-Am Cup and you 're not skiing today ?
#Text=DNF , so nothing else for the rest of the afternoon now .
#Text=So how have you preformed in the past days ?
#Text=I 've done pretty well in the previous days .
#Text=I 've finished every race till now which has been good , I 've improved my points on what I 've had previously , so I 'm progressing slowly and , yeah , it 's good .
#Text=Are you shooting for Sochi or are you just kind of developing now with the idea of the next one [ Winter Paralympics ] in 2018 ?
#Text=I 'd like to go to Sochi , but realistically it 's probably not going to happen , I 've only been skiing for three years , so .
#Text=And you 're from some town that 's really hard to pronounce in Australia .
#Text=So Victoria is the state that produces all the great Australian skiers ?
#Text=Correct , Victoria is the state to be in .
#Text=How long have you been in the development team ?
#Text=Been skiing for almost three years now .
#Text=On the development team or just period ?
#Text=Period but I pretty much got onto the development team [ ... ] days in[ ? ] , so all my skiing has been with the team .
#Text=You never considered doing the nordic skiing ?
#Text=Where do you like to ski and which , like Super G , Slalom , is your favourite ?
#Text=would be the one I 've enjoyed most so far .
#Text=It 's fast , obviously , a speed event , and the whole build-up to it , ' s really fun and I enjoy the speed events .
#Text=Are you one of these people likes to come to the US , or do you think Victoria 's got the best ski fields in the world ?
#Text=US is pretty good , I 've sort of skied quite a few hills .
#Text=I 've based somewhere different each year so far . [ ... ]
#Text=I do n't really have a preferred one .
#Text=Considering how expensive skiing is , do you think you 're getting adequate support from everyone to enable you to continue your ski career ?
#Text=Yeah , at the moment I 'm getting good support from the team and everyone , which is really good and hopefully financially I can keep doing it into the future .
#Text=As someone watching skiing : can you throw your monoski over your shoulder and transport it that way ?
#Text=I can if I want to but I 've got a set of wheels that I clip the rig into so I can push it around more easily than putting it on me shoulder .
#Text=I cart skis[ ? ] around on my shoulder , but I 've got a set of wheels , just to make it easier .
